<h3>Pros:</h3>
<ul class="pro">
<li>Absorbs liquid on contact, forming hard clumps.</li>
<li>Clumps are easy to scoop and flushable for disposal.</li>
<li>Very low dust and non-tracking.</li>
<li>Pleasant lavender scent helps cover litter box odors.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Cons:</h3>
<ul class="con">
<li>Litter may take on an unpleasant odor when exposed to a significant amount of urine.</li>
<li>Some cats find the lavender scent unpleasant or too strong.</li>
</ul>
<p>This litter comes in 7, 14, and 28-pound bags. Because the litter is made from compressed corn rather than clay, it is lightweight compared to most traditional cat litters.</p>
</div>
<h2>What Do Customers Think of World’s Best Cat Litter?</h2>
<p>Pet owners are a picky bunch, to be sure. When it comes to products like cat litter, there are certain basic requirements that must be met in order to satisfy a cat owner. For the most part, World’s Best Cat Litter meets or exceeds these requirements, and customers are largely satisfied with the brand.</p>
<p>This being said, every customer’s experience is unique, and there are both good and bad reviews for the brand online. Keep reading to see a positive and negative customer review for each of the three cat litter formulas featured above:</p>
<h3>Positive Customer Reviews for World’s Best Cat Litter</h3>
<p><em>“I love this cat litter. I made the switch after discovering that most traditional litters contain silica, which when inhaled over time, can cause lung diseases including cancer. I thought, what do I have to lose? With a name like World’s Best Cat Litter, maybe it really was good stuff! Well, it sure is. This litter is literally just ground up dried corn. That is it. It is magical, clumps very tightly, and doesn’t have little bits breaking off and crumbling away. My cats had zero issues adjusting to their new litter.” </em>&#8211;<strong> CaitlinCatLady</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-scoopable%2Fdp%2F37593" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Scoopable Multiple Cat Clumping Formula</a></p>
<p><em>“Highly recommend the World’s Best green bag formula! I’ve used this product for 12 years with two cats. We are sensitive to smells and wanted to easily clean the litter box. A friend recommended this – it’s so easy to flush feces daily (or hourly)! Clumps well too. I tried the multi-cat formula once but seemed to have a perfume/odor. This green bag formula doesn’t have odors and works great.” </em><strong>-Julia</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-clumping%2Fdp%2F37468" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Clumping Formula</a></p>
<p><em>“Happy customer! This stuff is awesome! My 2 cats with 3 litter boxes means a lot of scooping. This is the easiest, cleanest litter to scoop. Pee clumps quickly, but doesn’t stick to the box, just to the waste! Even if your cat, like mine, pees at the very edge of the box, you’ll scoop the clump without any scraping or chipping away to dislodge it from the box. It lifts right out.” </em>&#8211; <strong>Cleaner</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-lavender%2Fdp%2F37591" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Lavender Scented Multiple Cat Clumping Formula</a></p>
<h3>Negative Customer Reviews for World’s Best Cat Litter</h3>
<p><em>“My cat is a Maine Coon. He is huge and makes a lot of urine. He was too big for this litter… The urinated litter sticks to the bottom of the pan like goo. He is so big he also tracked it around the bathroom. I used to clean the box and floor every day or two… I don’t advise this for an adult cat whose urine comes out like a race horse. But a small cat is okay.”  </em>&#8211; <strong>Pippinsmom</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-scoopable%2Fdp%2F37593" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Scoopable Multiple Cat Clumping Formula</a></p>
<p><em>“This litter works very well right out of the bag. It forms tight clumps and traps odors. I never smelled anything! However, a few weeks of just topping off the litter when I scooped as needed, I noticed the litter overall was turning into a fine dust. This dust ends up everywhere plus the litter tracks far and wide. I always assume clumping litter will track, and I will say this is not nearly as bad as clay litter.” </em>&#8211; <strong>CatOwner</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-clumping%2Fdp%2F37468" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Clumping Formula</a></p>
<p><em>“My first impression is the lavender smell is not great. Second, it does not hide smells it more mixes with the smells and creates an even worse smell. I was using basic clay litter from my local store before, it was way cheaper, and I never smelled the litter box. With this litter, I smell it all through the house. However, it is really easy to clean! It clumps really well.” </em>&#8211; <strong>Imalady</strong>, reviewing <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:worlds-best-cat-litter-review/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fworlds-best-cat-litter-lavender%2Fdp%2F37591" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener">World’s Best Lavender Scented Multiple Cat Clumping Formula</a></p>
<h2>How Much Does World’s Best Cat Litter Cost?</h2>
<p>Many cat litters made from natural materials are more expensive than traditional clay litters, but that is not the case with World’s Best Cat Litter.</p>
<p>This brand is similarly priced to traditional litters, but you actually get more for your money due to the concentrated power of naturally absorbent corn materials. A small bag of World’s Best Cat Litter lasts one cat 30 days or longer because it is low-waste and would normally cost between <strong>$1.1-$1.2 per pound</strong>.</p>
