</li>
<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-39705">
<article id="comment-39705" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e66f4557e1025afde42c6618bcf9138a?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e66f4557e1025afde42c6618bcf9138a?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Stephany Farrell</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/worlds-best-cat-litter-review#comment-39705"><time datetime="2020-05-02T16:05:13+00:00">May 2, 2020 at 4:05 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I found this brand while looking for kitten attract litter. I foster, and things can get messy! It&#8217;s so light and clumps so well and quickly! It does have a fine dust if you don&#8217;t switch out the whole pan for a while, all the smaller stuff gets left behind when you scoop out clumps. Honestly though, I didn&#8217;t realize it was corn based until after I bought it, so the Eco friendly makes even more attractive. I feel that, even though the price is higher than I would like to pay (as a foster mom), it&#8217;s worth it when it helps the kittens learn to go NOT ON THE FLOOR! LOL! I would consider buying it for all my cats if I could buy it in bulk &amp; cheaper!</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-39705' data-commentid="39705" data-postid="10110" data-belowelement="comment-39705" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Stephany Farrell" aria-label='Reply to Stephany Farrell'>Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div>
