<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-39707">
<article id="comment-39707" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/de19a923e8288ebf170efbc7e9e67daa?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/de19a923e8288ebf170efbc7e9e67daa?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Jean</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/worlds-best-cat-litter-review#comment-39707"><time datetime="2020-05-02T20:55:31+00:00">May 2, 2020 at 8:55 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I bought this on the recommendation of a friend, eco friendly, low dust, lasts long time. I have one cat and I scoop the box morning and night. Yes, there was a minimum of dust when filling the box, but the foul/sour odor that remains after my cat urinates is off putting and it doesn&#8217;t go away after scooping the clumps out. When I used clay litter, there was never an odor. After I finish the bags I have, I will probably go back to Dr. Easley&#8217;s litter.</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-39707' data-commentid="39707" data-postid="10110" data-belowelement="comment-39707" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jean" aria-label='Reply to Jean'>Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div>
