</li>
<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-67202">
<article id="comment-67202" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/62f0c2433583484c6886e7351d32cc3e?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/62f0c2433583484c6886e7351d32cc3e?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Robert Oehlschlager</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/worlds-best-cat-litter-review#comment-67202"><time datetime="2021-11-07T14:44:58+00:00">Nov 7, 2021 at 2:44 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>There must be a bentonite clay supply chain issue with COVID 19 because the ultra expensive ($17 a bag) cat litter products were the only ones on the shelf. I had no choice but select America&#8217;s Best or go hunting down a bentonite clay based litter box filler. Instead of blowing $3-$4 on cat box filler, I had to blow nearly $20.<br />
I don&#8217;t scoop, I discard the entire contents of the litter box.<br />
My cats started using the cat litter and stopped after 2-3 days.<br />
World&#8217;s best cat litter has been the absolute worst cat litter product I&#8217;ve ever used.<br />
Urine glues litter/urine to the bottom of the litter box making cleaning a HUGE problem.<br />
The World&#8217;s Best Cat Litter is absolutely proven itself to be the world&#8217;s worst cat litter in actuality.<br />
I&#8217;ll never buy another bag, EVER.</p>
</section>
